t cake, Glut, Good Food, Icing, Loaf tin, Make ahead, Olympics, Overripe, Team gb, Traditional, Weekend, Winning treats","publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Good Food","url":"https://www.bbcgoodfood.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","height":325,"url":"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2026/02/goodfood.logo-f37096c.png?resize=1312,325","width":1312}},"cookTime":"PT50M","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"268 calories","fatContent":"13 grams fat","saturatedFatContent":"8 grams saturated fat","carbohydrateContent":"34 grams carbohydrates","sugarContent":"24 grams sugar","fiberContent":"1 grams fiber","proteinContent":"3 grams protein","sodiumContent":"0.5 milligram of sodium"},"prepTime":"PT15M","recipeCategory":"Afternoon tea, Dessert","recipeCuisine":"British","recipeIngredient":["140g butter softened, plus extra for the tin","140g caster sugar","2 large eggs beaten","140g self-raising flour","1 tsp baking powder","2 very ripe  bananas mashed","50g icing sugar","handful dried banana chips for decoration"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4. Butter a 2lb loaf tin and line the base and sides with baking parchment.","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2013/04/1.-Lining-tin-0b46cdd.jpg","width":1000,"height":667}},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cream 140g softened butter and 140g caster sugar until light and fluffy, then slowly add 2 beaten large eggs with a little of the 140g flour.","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2013/04/2.-Creamed-sugar-and-egg-v2-61a46fb.jpg","width":1000,"height":667}},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Fold in the remaining flour, 1 tsp baking powder and 2 mashed bananas.","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2013/04/4.-Add-flour-banana-v2-4e08754.jpg","width":1000,"height":667}},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Pour the mixture into the prepared tin and bake for about 50 mins, or until cooked through. Check the loaf at 5-min intervals from around 30-40 mins in the oven by testing it with a skewer (it should be able to be inserted and removed cleanly), as the time may vary depending on the shape of your loaf tin.","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2025/02/5.-Mixture-in-tin-v2-64c2ad3.jpg","width":1000,"height":667}},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cool in the tin for 10 mins, then remove to a wire rack."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Mix 50g icing sugar with 2-3 tsp water to make a runny icing.","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2025/02/6.-Icing-sugar-v2-edea1e6.jpg","width":1000,"height":666}},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Drizzle the icing across the top of the cake and decorate with a handful of banana chips.","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2025/02/7.-Icing-sugar-drizzle-v3-debe7fc.jpg","width":1000,"height":667}}],"recipeYield":"Cuts into 8-10 slices","totalTime":"PT1H5M"}</script><div class="post recipe" data-gtm-class="recipe-template" data-content-type="recipe" data-item-id="233531" data-item-name="Banana bread" data-testid="post"><nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="breadcrumb hidden-print mt-sm mb-sm container"><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org/","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Recipes","item":"https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Banana bread"}]}</script><ul class="breadcrumb__list body-copy-extra-small oflow-x-auto list"><li class="breadcrumb__item list-item"><i class="breadcrumb__icon mr-xs icon" style="width:11px;min-width